text: Building an MS Access database using python
A primary goal of a project I plan to bid on involves creating a Microsoft Access database using python.
The main DB backend will be postgres, but the plan is to export an Access image.
This will be a web app that'll take input from the user and go through a black box and output the results as an access db.
The web app will be built on a linux server.
I have a few related questions:

lis.text: Is there a reliable library or module that can be used?
What has your experience been using Access and python?
Any tips, tricks, or must avoids I need to know about?
